too bad , too sad i want to change the world sounds noble enough but with the fluff in between these covers , this & quot ; world changer & quot ; has some time , if ever , to go until he can lay any claim to this . karims fellow designers should be outraged by his presentation of their industry as being so fickle , tranparent and thin . a real shame given the power that products have in our lives and to our cultures . do not buy this book